=Show Alarms=
This operation is used to view Alarm information

==Request==
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Method || GET
|-
|Request URI || 
/unc/alarms
|-
|Query String ||
 ?alarm_no={alarm_no}
|}

;Description of request URI elements
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Element || Description || Required
|-
|alarm_no || Alarm number.
Valid value: Decimal number.
Valid range: 1 - 9999999999999999999
||Yes
|}

==Response==
;Response Body
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Response Body ||
*XML format
 <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
 <alarms>
   <alarm
     alarm_no="{alarm_no}"
     timestamp="{timestamp}"
     severity="{severity}"
     type="{type}"
     vtn_name="{vtn_name}"
     summary="{summary}"
     message="{message}"/>
   </alarms>
*JSON format
 {
  "alarms": [
  {
     "alarm_no": "{alarm_no}",
     "timestamp": "{timestamp}",
     "severity": "{severity}",
     "type": "{type}",
     "vtn_name": "{vtn_name}",
     "summary": "{summary}",
     "message": "{message}"
   }
  ]
 }
|}

=Clear Alarms=
This operation is used to clear Alarm information.

==Request==
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Method || PUT
|-
|Request URI || 
/unc/alarms
|-
|Query String ||
 ?alarm_no={alarm_no}
|}

==Response==
;Response Body
:None

;Description of response elements
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Element || Description
|-
|alarm_no || Alarm number.
Valid value: Decimal number.
Valid range: 1 - 9999999999999999999
|-
|timestamp || Occurrence time.
Valid value: UNIX time (The elapsed time in seconds since
00:00:00 UTC, 1 January, 1970).
|-
|severity || Severity
Valid value: emergency, alert, critical, error, warning, notice,
information, debug
|-
|type || Alarm type.
Valid value: occurred, recovered
|-
|vtn_name || VTN name.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters including alphanumeric
characters and underscore (except at the beginning).
|-
|summary || Alarm summary.
Valid value: Up to 95 characters.
|-
|message ||Alarm message.
Valid value: Up to 511 characters.
|}
